2
00:00:42.308 --> 00:00:46.369
DORM
I still remember the first time I left home.

3
00:00:51.484 --> 00:00:54.681
It was a Sunday afternoon...

4
00:00:54.754 --> 00:00:56.619
that felt both hectic and lonely.

5
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:02.153
It was the last day...

6
00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:07.295
of the mid-term break for me
and my seventh grade friends.

7
00:01:10.336 --> 00:01:12.429
It felt like the last day of freedom...

8
00:01:13.206 --> 00:01:16.539
A freedom we'd come to enjoy during our vacation.

9
00:01:17.444 --> 00:01:18.274
Stop crying!

10
00:01:18.645 --> 00:01:19.942
You didn't get any work done over vacation.

11
00:01:25.285 --> 00:01:26.547
One thing I felt that...

12
00:01:27.587 --> 00:01:31.648
I'd never come to terms with is...

13
00:01:32.125 --> 00:01:33.558
- How do you want it cut. handsome?
- Crew cut.

14
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:36.494
the last day of vacation...

15
00:01:43.269 --> 00:01:43.928
Even so...

16
00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:46.998
some of us can't wait for school to re-open...

17
00:01:49.242 --> 00:01:51.267
because it means being
reunited with our friends.

18
00:01:58.184 --> 00:01:58.946
Except for me.

19
00:02:10.063 --> 00:02:11.428
Hey! Stop pressing the buttons!

20
00:02:36.256 --> 00:02:38.588
Jaew! Pen! Take good care of the house!

21
00:02:38.992 --> 00:02:39.924
Yes. ma'am.

22
00:02:48.434 --> 00:02:50.603
You know. we could've waited for Ton...

23
00:02:50.638 --> 00:02:53.037
to finish 7th grade before
transferring him to another school.

24
00:02:54.340 --> 00:02:57.443
The sudden move is a shock for me as well.

25
00:02:57.478 --> 00:02:59.741
Listen. this isn't open for discussion. understand?

26
00:03:01.114 --> 00:03:03.048
Ton's new school is up-country right. Dad?

27
00:03:03.349 --> 00:03:04.441
Yes. it's in Chonburi. son.

28
00:03:05.351 --> 00:03:07.148
Where will he sleep?

29
00:03:07.453 --> 00:03:08.545
In the school dormitory.

30
00:03:09.422 --> 00:03:10.252
They have everything there.

31
00:03:11.124 --> 00:03:13.786
Remember. son. a man
must be able to live anywhere.

32
00:03:18.464 --> 00:03:19.863
Are we almost there?

33
00:03:20.633 --> 00:03:22.328
No. we have to cross the Bangpakong River first.

34
00:03:23.803 --> 00:03:25.236
Hurry up and make a wish. Toh!

35
00:03:25.305 --> 00:03:26.863
If you hold your breath as we cross the bridge...

36
00:03:27.140 --> 00:03:30.810
whatever you wish for will come true.

37
00:03:30.845 --> 00:03:31.469
Really. Mom?

38
00:03:31.811 --> 00:03:34.644
But don't cheat and sneak a breath first.

39
00:03:34.747 --> 00:03:35.771
Ton. hold your breath too.

40
00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:01.864
What did you wish for?

41
00:04:05.678 --> 00:04:08.306
For Dad to send me to boarding school with Ton.

42
00:04:11.184 --> 00:04:12.651
How about you. Ton?

43
00:04:18.625 --> 00:04:21.856
Saichon Witaya School

44
00:04:42.715 --> 00:04:44.205
Toh. play around here. okay?

45
00:05:12.045 --> 00:05:14.479
Student Dormitory

46
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:22.219
Good afternoon. Teacher.

47
00:05:23.256 --> 00:05:24.450
I'm Miss Pranee...

48
00:05:25.258 --> 00:05:27.249
the dorm master for junior high boys.

49
00:05:28.594 --> 00:05:29.526
This must be Chatree.

50
00:05:30.463 --> 00:05:31.293
Yes. ma'am.

51
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:33.890
Parents. please wait here.

52
00:05:34.801 --> 00:05:36.894
Chatree. follow me. please.

53
00:05:42.675 --> 00:05:43.664
Don't dilly dally now.

54
00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.646
Hey. it's a new kid.

55
00:05:57.457 --> 00:05:58.651
Where's he from?

56
00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:02.325
He seems like a troublemaker.

57
00:06:16.476 --> 00:06:17.773
This is your bed.

58
00:06:18.311 --> 00:06:19.938
Go collect your blanket.

59
00:06:21.314 --> 00:06:25.148
Make sure to make your bed every morning.

60
00:06:26.152 --> 00:06:27.949
Every boy must take care of himself here.

61
00:06:28.488 --> 00:06:31.946
No one will serve you or
pamper you like you were at home.

62
00:06:44.604 --> 00:06:46.299
Dad has written your name on everything.

63
00:06:49.675 --> 00:06:50.539
Study hard. son.

64
00:06:51.344 --> 00:06:52.811
Don't get into trouble. okay?

65
00:06:57.350 --> 00:06:58.214
Please keep an eye on him.

66
00:06:59.685 --> 00:07:00.310
I will.

67
00:08:21.968 --> 00:08:22.798
Don't be so noisy.

68
00:08:49.228 --> 00:08:51.253
Chatree. follow me.

69
00:08:59.906 --> 00:09:01.840
Dinner is served at 6 p.m.

70
00:09:02.775 --> 00:09:04.208
Everyone must eat on time.

71
00:09:06.612 --> 00:09:08.876
This is your seat. Sit down.

72
00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:33.262
Next term. I'm sending Ton to boarding school.

73
00:09:37.143 --> 00:09:39.304
Why the sudden decision to send him away?

74
00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:41.308
Mother...

75
00:09:41.714 --> 00:09:44.512
this new school has high
standards and a good reputation...

76
00:09:45.718 --> 00:09:46.810
unlike his current school.

77
00:09:47.653 --> 00:09:49.086
The kids don't study hard enough.

78
00:09:49.889 --> 00:09:53.154
Before exams. they play around and watch TV.

79
00:09:53.392 --> 00:09:54.654
But they still get good grades.

80
00:09:55.828 --> 00:09:57.762
That means the school has low standards.

81
00:10:24.357 --> 00:10:25.153
This is Chatree.

82
00:10:26.592 --> 00:10:27.650
Your new classmate.

83
00:10:29.629 --> 00:10:31.688
Chatree will board here and study with us...

84
00:10:32.131 --> 00:10:33.530
starting from this term.

85
00:10:37.203 --> 00:10:38.135
Go take your seat.

86
00:11:07.767 --> 00:11:09.132
Chatree. Master Peng is calling.

87
00:11:13.406 --> 00:11:14.373
My name's Peng.

88
00:11:16.008 --> 00:11:16.906
That's Dr. Nui.

89
00:11:19.578 --> 00:11:21.307
This idiot is Sarote.

90
00:11:22.615 --> 00:11:24.207
That ass is Pok.

91
00:11:25.184 --> 00:11:26.116
I'm Toei.

92
00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:31.615
What's your name?

93
00:11:32.458 --> 00:11:33.390
Chatree.

94
00:11:34.193 --> 00:11:35.592
His name's Chatree.

95
00:11:36.162 --> 00:11:37.186
Okay. Chatree.

96
00:11:38.130 --> 00:11:40.257
Are you scared of ghosts?

97
00:11:40.633 --> 00:11:42.225
Of course. why wouldn't he be?

98
00:11:43.803 --> 00:11:45.464
I'm not asking you. idiot.

99
00:11:47.073 --> 00:11:48.563
Are you scared of ghosts?

100
00:11:50.876 --> 00:11:53.276
Good. As we've been here longer...

101
00:11:54.046 --> 00:11:56.344
we're gonna tell you the history of our school.

102
00:12:01.921 --> 00:12:03.445
I just found out myself.

103
00:12:04.156 --> 00:12:05.953
I'm sure you guys haven't heard it.

104
00:12:08.794 --> 00:12:11.160
A senior told me that...

105
00:12:11.997 --> 00:12:14.966
one of the cooks had a beautiful daughter.

106
00:12:18.337 --> 00:12:20.965
She was the crush of every boy in the school.

107
00:12:27.513 --> 00:12:28.343
But one day...

108
00:12:30.015 --> 00:12:31.812
she hung herself...

109
00:12:32.852 --> 00:12:34.319
from a Po tree.

110
00:12:38.290 --> 00:12:42.124
No one knew why she suddenly killed herself.

111
00:12:42.895 --> 00:12:44.988
When the police conducted an autopsy...

112
00:12:45.898 --> 00:12:48.366
they discovered that she was...

113
00:12:50.669 --> 00:12:52.034
four months pregnant.

114
00:12:55.541 --> 00:12:57.338
A pregnant ghost is the nastiest kind around.

115
00:12:58.144 --> 00:13:00.840
The story goes. a group of senior boys...

116
00:13:01.547 --> 00:13:02.741
wanted to find out the truth.

117
00:13:03.115 --> 00:13:05.583
One... two... three...

118
00:13:07.052 --> 00:13:07.950
What did they see?

119
00:13:34.013 --> 00:13:35.275
No need to go to the Po tree.

120
00:13:38.751 --> 00:13:39.718
There are ghosts in the dorm.

121
00:13:40.986 --> 00:13:42.544
Someone once saw an old man...

122
00:13:42.888 --> 00:13:44.685
walking around the dorms at night.

123
00:13:50.329 --> 00:13:52.388
At first. no one knew who he was.

124
00:13:53.365 --> 00:13:56.266
But when they looked in old yearbooks...

125
00:13:57.169 --> 00:13:58.033
they found out that...

126
00:13:59.271 --> 00:14:01.262
he used to be the dorm master.

127
00:14:05.911 --> 00:14:07.674
You've got the chills. Master Peng.

128
00:14:08.514 --> 00:14:09.913
Hey... bugger off.

129
00:14:10.783 --> 00:14:12.273
Have you guys ever noticed...

130
00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:15.551
that if you pee in the bathroom at night...

131
00:14:16.088 --> 00:14:18.352
it seems like you're not alone.

132
00:14:40.746 --> 00:14:41.474
Remember...

133
00:14:42.147 --> 00:14:44.445
Any night the dogs howl in unison...

134
00:14:44.984 --> 00:14:47.145
stay away from the bathrooms.

135
00:14:54.426 --> 00:14:55.358
Hey. do you guys know...

136
00:14:56.161 --> 00:14:58.595
why our school had to build a new swimming pool?

137
00:15:02.101 --> 00:15:03.830
Because a student drowned himself...

138
00:15:05.204 --> 00:15:07.195
in the old pool behind the school.

139
00:15:12.244 --> 00:15:13.142
Did you know...

140
00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:15.972
he was in 7th grade just like us?

141
00:15:18.651 --> 00:15:19.675
Most importantly...

142
00:15:21.787 --> 00:15:23.277
he used to board in this dorm.

143
00:15:25.157 --> 00:15:27.955
So they shut down the pool years ago.

144
00:15:29.628 --> 00:15:31.061
A senior told me that...

145
00:15:31.630 --> 00:15:34.565
Miss Pranee almost went mad.

146
00:15:38.871 --> 00:15:40.736
Yeah. that's when she became weird.

147
00:15:41.540 --> 00:15:43.940
And she still hasn't recovered.

148
00:15:45.010 --> 00:15:47.843
Do you know how weird she is?

149
00:15:53.185 --> 00:15:56.746
Have you seen the old record player in her office?

150
00:15:58.490 --> 00:16:01.015
She likes to listen to this one sappy love song.

151
00:16:02.728 --> 00:16:04.161
It gives me the creeps.

152
00:16:08.567 --> 00:16:10.228
One day...

153
00:16:11.837 --> 00:16:12.531
someone saw...

154
00:16:13.405 --> 00:16:16.374
Miss Pranee staring and crying at an open drawer.

155
00:16:33.559 --> 00:16:34.685
To this day...

156
00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:36.354
nobody knows...

157
00:16:36.862 --> 00:16:39.854
what the hell is in that drawer.

158
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:41.758
Maybe there's a magic genie.

159
00:16:42.701 --> 00:16:44.828
Magic genie. my ass.

160
00:16:50.242 --> 00:16:51.140
After awhile...

161
00:16:52.211 --> 00:16:54.111
you'll see for yourself. Chatree.

162
00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:02.348
I bet that...

163
00:17:03.088 --> 00:17:08.754
Miss Pranee had something
to do with the boy's death.

164
00:17:10.229 --> 00:17:13.027
And that boy's ghost is a vicious one.

165
00:17:14.066 --> 00:17:15.499
Anyone who slept in his bed...

166
00:17:15.934 --> 00:17:18.698
was kicked out of it every night.

167
00:17:19.405 --> 00:17:21.873
Finally. they had to put the bed in the storage.

168
00:17:25.477 --> 00:17:26.034
But...

169
00:17:27.846 --> 00:17:32.749
I saw the janitor bring his
bed out from the storage today.

170
00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:35.409
Boys!

171
00:17:36.922 --> 00:17:38.355
Bed time is for sleeping.

172
00:17:39.258 --> 00:17:41.055
Anyone who can't wake up tomorrow...

173
00:17:42.061 --> 00:17:43.050
will get whacked.

174
00:20:41.506 --> 00:20:43.531
Hey... the new kid wet his bed!

175
00:20:43.709 --> 00:20:47.941
All grown up and still wetting his bed.

176
00:20:48.614 --> 00:20:51.879
The new boy wet his bed!

177
00:21:03.528 --> 00:21:04.153
Damn it!

178
00:21:31.223 --> 00:21:33.054
Hey... if you hang it up that way...

179
00:21:33.325 --> 00:21:34.724
it'll just fall to the ground.

180
00:21:36.361 --> 00:21:39.023
The clothesline is a battle zone.

181
00:21:39.498 --> 00:21:42.092
If you're going to make space you have to be tricky.

182
00:21:45.737 --> 00:21:47.364
And you only need one pair of bathing shorts.

183
00:21:47.706 --> 00:21:51.403
One pair will suffice.
Or else every pair will get moldy.

184
00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:14.765
Hey. do you guys smell something?

185
00:22:16.802 --> 00:22:17.461
No...

186
00:22:19.137 --> 00:22:20.069
That's not it.

187
00:22:30.015 --> 00:22:31.414
I know. It reeks of his piss.

188
00:22:32.784 --> 00:22:35.981
I see all the ghost stories
made you wet your pants.

189
00:22:38.924 --> 00:22:40.892
Make fun of the new boy. everyone.

190
00:22:47.532 --> 00:22:49.034
Pok. why are you laughing?

191
00:22:49.069 --> 00:22:50.296
Your mouth stinks pretty bad as well.

192
00:22:55.407 --> 00:22:56.203
Is it broken?

193
00:22:57.376 --> 00:22:59.105
I don't know. Maybe I can fix it.

194
00:23:00.479 --> 00:23:01.503
You know how to fix it?

195
00:23:03.248 --> 00:23:04.647
I'm not sure but I'll try.

196
00:23:07.185 --> 00:23:08.311
can I try playing it?

197
00:23:09.020 --> 00:23:09.452
Sure.

198
00:23:10.689 --> 00:23:13.453
Chatree. you have a phone call.

199
00:23:14.192 --> 00:23:15.284
It's your dad.

200
00:23:25.504 --> 00:23:30.441
Chatree Anantpitisuk. your
father is on the dormitory phone.

201
00:23:31.009 --> 00:23:35.275
Chatree Anantpitisuk. your
father is on the dormitory phone.

202
00:23:47.459 --> 00:23:48.585
I brought you some sweets.

203
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.683
Don't let me catch you again.

204
00:24:14.219 --> 00:24:16.016
If you get bad grades this year...

205
00:24:16.154 --> 00:24:17.143
I'll really punish you.

206
00:24:40.712 --> 00:24:42.703
Chatree isn't here right now.

207
00:24:43.448 --> 00:24:44.779
Would you like to leave a message?

208
00:24:47.586 --> 00:24:49.816
No. that's okay. I'll call back another day.

209
00:24:50.388 --> 00:24:51.719
Thank you.

210
00:27:20.905 --> 00:27:21.929
Hey... who's there!

211
00:27:22.474 --> 00:27:23.304
Open the door!

212
00:27:25.910 --> 00:27:27.878
Asshole. just wait until I get out!

213
00:27:29.447 --> 00:27:30.175
Hey!

214
00:27:31.182 --> 00:27:32.376
Open the door!

215
00:27:39.290 --> 00:27:40.484
That was awesome.

216
00:27:40.625 --> 00:27:42.650
Just a few ghost tales and he peed his pants.

217
00:27:43.028 --> 00:27:44.495
What a sucker!

218
00:27:53.705 --> 00:27:54.797
Hey. open it please.

219
00:31:13.304 --> 00:31:13.702
Hey...

220
00:31:15.039 --> 00:31:15.835
Woke up late?

221
00:31:16.541 --> 00:31:16.973
Yeah.

222
00:31:21.746 --> 00:31:24.715
You're real curious about Miss Pranee. aren't you?

223
00:31:26.117 --> 00:31:27.106
Watch out. okay.

224
00:31:32.156 --> 00:31:32.622
Sure.

225
00:31:33.391 --> 00:31:36.189
Do you know why Miss Pranee's so weird?

226
00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:39.892
There are lots of theories.

227
00:31:40.965 --> 00:31:42.592
Worst of all are the ghost stories.

228
00:31:43.368 --> 00:31:44.357
They're not true.

229
00:31:46.070 --> 00:31:46.968
Been here long?

230
00:31:49.007 --> 00:31:49.769
Yeah. why?

231
00:31:51.843 --> 00:31:52.605
No reason.

232
00:31:53.211 --> 00:31:54.269
You seem to know it all.

233
00:31:55.346 --> 00:31:56.540
Of course I do!

234
00:31:56.848 --> 00:32:00.511
Don't you know I'm
Vichien 'Know-It-All' Chumchong!

235
00:32:02.020 --> 00:32:03.715
Hurry up and take a bath.

236
00:32:04.122 --> 00:32:05.111
Miss Pranee is coming down.

237
00:32:13.731 --> 00:32:15.255
Before we go down for breakfast...

238
00:32:16.234 --> 00:32:17.633
I have something to say.

239
00:32:19.370 --> 00:32:21.861
This is a school not a graveyard.

240
00:32:23.708 --> 00:32:27.166
I want you to stop telling
ghost stories to scare each other.

241
00:32:29.614 --> 00:32:33.380
If I catch anyone engaging in such nonsense...

242
00:32:35.053 --> 00:32:36.714
don't say you weren't warned.

243
00:32:42.760 --> 00:32:45.092
Chatree. wait up!

244
00:32:46.597 --> 00:32:47.723
What are you daydreaming about?

245
00:32:57.141 --> 00:32:58.267
Have you ever snuck out of school?

246
00:33:00.011 --> 00:33:00.739
Where to?

247
00:33:01.746 --> 00:33:02.508
Home. of course.

248
00:33:04.449 --> 00:33:04.915
What for?

249
00:33:05.450 --> 00:33:06.508
School is more fun than home.

250
00:33:07.318 --> 00:33:08.979
No parents to tell you what to do.

251
00:33:10.054 --> 00:33:11.180
Fun as hell. it is.

252
00:33:14.926 --> 00:33:16.723
It's hard at first but you'll get used to it.

253
00:33:19.063 --> 00:33:20.189
No. I won't.

254
00:33:25.103 --> 00:33:26.161
Do you see what I see?

255
00:33:29.407 --> 00:33:29.896
Geese?

256
00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:32.801
Look again.

257
00:33:35.947 --> 00:33:38.108
Oh... there are goose eggs!

258
00:33:42.120 --> 00:33:43.747
Calm down. little bro.

259
00:33:46.057 --> 00:33:47.957
Geese are really protective of their eggs.

260
00:33:49.527 --> 00:33:51.085
If you want to steal them...

261
00:33:52.130 --> 00:33:53.222
there's only one way.

262
00:33:56.768 --> 00:33:57.894
Hurry up. man.

263
00:34:05.309 --> 00:34:06.003
Hurry up!

264
00:34:07.412 --> 00:34:08.106
Hurry!

265
00:34:13.518 --> 00:34:14.212
Hurry!

266
00:34:22.126 --> 00:34:23.115
I got them!

267
00:34:28.132 --> 00:34:28.996
Chatree...

268
00:34:32.970 --> 00:34:34.232
your father's on the phone.

269
00:34:39.710 --> 00:34:40.642
Hold on. please.

270
00:34:40.812 --> 00:34:41.403
Yes.

271
00:34:44.015 --> 00:34:44.947
I'll see you later. okay.

272
00:34:45.483 --> 00:34:46.074
Sure.

273
00:36:26.117 --> 00:36:29.484
Chatree. grab a seat for us
in the courtyard after dinner.

274
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:31.818
There's an outdoor film screening tonight.

